Sam Allardyce believes Manchester City manager Manuel Pellegrini has the most difficult job in football . 
  West Ham United face City at the Etihad Stadium on Sunday . 
  The Hammers boss believes the pressure of winning back-to-back Premier League titles has made the job harder . 
  Manchester City have come under fire after a poor run of form . 
  Financial Fair Play rules have also put pressure on the Chilean . 
 